&lt;p&gt;My core expertise lies in &lt;strong&gt;Go&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Python&lt;/strong&gt;, but I&amp;rsquo;m a &lt;strong&gt;full-stack&lt;/strong&gt; developer at heart,&lt;br&gt;
comfortable with everything from cloud infrastructure and DevOps with &lt;strong&gt;Kubernetes&lt;/strong&gt; to front-end development with &lt;strong&gt;React&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;TypeScript&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Throughout my career at companies like &lt;strong&gt;SAP&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;NetEase Games&lt;/strong&gt;, I&amp;rsquo;ve led the development of critical systemsâ€”from high-traffic game features serving hundreds of thousands of daily players to infrastructure platforms that secured production environments and saved hundreds of thousands of dollars in cloud costs annually.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&amp;rsquo;m driven by a strong sense of product ownership and a passion for turning ideas into reality.&lt;br&gt;
This led me to become an independent developer, where I now build my own products, such as an automated stock trading bot and open-source financial tools.&lt;br&gt;
